WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.409 align:middle line:90%
[THEME MUSIC]

00:00:03.409 --> 00:00:18.188 align:middle line:90%


00:00:18.188 --> 00:00:20.730 align:middle line:10%
>>GEORGE NOORY: And welcome to
this edition of Beyond Belief.

00:00:20.730 --> 00:00:22.780 align:middle line:10%
Nanci Trivellato is with us.

00:00:22.780 --> 00:00:25.830 align:middle line:10%
She has investigated
extraordinary phenomena

00:00:25.830 --> 00:00:28.770 align:middle line:10%
for more than three
decades, teaching thousands

00:00:28.770 --> 00:00:30.900 align:middle line:10%
around the world about
the theory and practice

00:00:30.900 --> 00:00:34.920 align:middle line:10%
of out-of-body experiences,
psychic awareness, and energy

00:00:34.920 --> 00:00:36.070 align:middle line:10%
sensitivity.

00:00:36.070 --> 00:00:39.390 align:middle line:84%
She is the author of
"Vibrational State and Energy

00:00:39.390 --> 00:00:42.930 align:middle line:84%
Resonance," and the co-founder
of the International

00:00:42.930 --> 00:00:45.180 align:middle line:90%
Academy of Consciousness.

00:00:45.180 --> 00:00:46.510 align:middle line:90%
That is fantastic.

00:00:46.510 --> 00:00:48.240 align:middle line:84%
How did you get
into this, Nanci?

00:00:48.240 --> 00:00:51.540 align:middle line:10%
>>NANCI TRIVELLATO: Well, when
I was around 20 years old,

00:00:51.540 --> 00:00:55.470 align:middle line:10%
I started searching
for studies on whatever

00:00:55.470 --> 00:00:58.020 align:middle line:10%
exists beyond physical world.

00:00:58.020 --> 00:01:00.900 align:middle line:10%
I couldn't agree
would be only this.

00:01:00.900 --> 00:01:04.830 align:middle line:10%
And what I noticed is that there
weren't many serious studies

00:01:04.830 --> 00:01:07.590 align:middle line:10%
at that time, quite long ago.

00:01:07.590 --> 00:01:11.970 align:middle line:84%
And I have had an
experience when I was young.

00:01:11.970 --> 00:01:13.470 align:middle line:84%
George, I'm going
to share with you

00:01:13.470 --> 00:01:15.390 align:middle line:84%
some highlights because
I think they are very

00:01:15.390 --> 00:01:17.380 align:middle line:90%
important to contextualize.

00:01:17.380 --> 00:01:19.780 align:middle line:84%
I am from a very
small town in Brazil.

00:01:19.780 --> 00:01:23.140 align:middle line:84%
One of those that you would
know everyone in town.

00:01:23.140 --> 00:01:24.730 align:middle line:90%
So that is more--

00:01:24.730 --> 00:01:25.900 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: 200 people, right?

00:01:25.900 --> 00:01:29.230 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: Well, maybe it was
like 1,000 at that time or so.

00:01:29.230 --> 00:01:32.380 align:middle line:84%
So when somebody would
pass away, at the church,

00:01:32.380 --> 00:01:34.940 align:middle line:84%
they would say, Oh, this person
passed away and everybody--

00:01:34.940 --> 00:01:36.190 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Everybody knew that.

00:01:36.190 --> 00:01:36.490 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Yes.

00:01:36.490 --> 00:01:37.840 align:middle line:90%
So everybody would know.

00:01:37.840 --> 00:01:41.440 align:middle line:84%
And I didn't have a
television set at home.

00:01:41.440 --> 00:01:44.440 align:middle line:90%
I didn't have many books.

00:01:44.440 --> 00:01:47.620 align:middle line:84%
I was from a not so
well-to-do family.

00:01:47.620 --> 00:01:53.140 align:middle line:84%
In that small city, we didn't
have cinema or a library

00:01:53.140 --> 00:01:54.530 align:middle line:90%
or anything like that.

00:01:54.530 --> 00:01:57.430 align:middle line:84%
And what happened is that when
I was around seven years old,

00:01:57.430 --> 00:02:01.990 align:middle line:84%
I had one of the experiences
that sometimes I used to have.

00:02:01.990 --> 00:02:04.630 align:middle line:84%
And my normal
experiences were such

00:02:04.630 --> 00:02:07.720 align:middle line:84%
that I would see my body
lying in bed, sleeping.

00:02:07.720 --> 00:02:11.470 align:middle line:84%
But I was so awake
that I could not make

00:02:11.470 --> 00:02:12.640 align:middle line:90%
sense of what was going on.

00:02:12.640 --> 00:02:13.973 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: And it wasn't a dream.

00:02:13.973 --> 00:02:14.773 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: No.

00:02:14.773 --> 00:02:15.760 align:middle line:90%
I was so awake.

00:02:15.760 --> 00:02:18.220 align:middle line:90%
Imagine at 6:00, 7:00.

00:02:18.220 --> 00:02:21.400 align:middle line:84%
That happened for quite
some few years at that age.

00:02:21.400 --> 00:02:26.440 align:middle line:84%
I would look and say,
I should be dreaming.

00:02:26.440 --> 00:02:28.330 align:middle line:90%
I should not be awake.

00:02:28.330 --> 00:02:31.000 align:middle line:84%
How can I be awake if
my body is sleeping?

00:02:31.000 --> 00:02:32.620 align:middle line:90%
It was that confusing.

00:02:32.620 --> 00:02:33.580 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Yeah, it is.

00:02:33.580 --> 00:02:38.065 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: And then next morning,
a kid playing, that's OK.

00:02:38.065 --> 00:02:39.190 align:middle line:90%
And I wouldn't think of it.

00:02:39.190 --> 00:02:40.107 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: No big deal.

00:02:40.107 --> 00:02:41.080 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: No big deal.

00:02:41.080 --> 00:02:45.070 align:middle line:84%
Until one time, I left
my body and I ended up

00:02:45.070 --> 00:02:49.360 align:middle line:84%
in São Paulo city, which is I
never been there and never seen

00:02:49.360 --> 00:02:51.400 align:middle line:90%
anything from São Paulo before.

00:02:51.400 --> 00:02:52.450 align:middle line:90%
It's a huge city.

00:02:52.450 --> 00:02:54.280 align:middle line:90%
Of course, everybody knows.

00:02:54.280 --> 00:02:58.480 align:middle line:84%
And many avenues
and huge buildings.

00:02:58.480 --> 00:03:03.940 align:middle line:84%
And I ended up in a room in a
hospital where an uncle of mine

00:03:03.940 --> 00:03:06.102 align:middle line:90%
was being operated or had--

00:03:06.102 --> 00:03:07.810 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: And you were
floating over him?

00:03:07.810 --> 00:03:08.610 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Yes.

00:03:08.610 --> 00:03:12.940 align:middle line:84%
And then I entered the hospital,
I was amazed what sort of place

00:03:12.940 --> 00:03:13.780 align:middle line:90%
is this.

00:03:13.780 --> 00:03:16.900 align:middle line:84%
And I ended up in that
room and I saw him.

00:03:16.900 --> 00:03:19.780 align:middle line:84%
It was a bit shocking,
but not fearful.

00:03:19.780 --> 00:03:24.610 align:middle line:84%
And he had a sheet
covering him and a kind

00:03:24.610 --> 00:03:29.270 align:middle line:84%
of a plastic tube like a
drain coming from his abdomen,

00:03:29.270 --> 00:03:32.470 align:middle line:84%
and directing like
a reddish liquid

00:03:32.470 --> 00:03:35.667 align:middle line:84%
to a glass jar that
was on the floor.

00:03:35.667 --> 00:03:37.000 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: That was blood, right?

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:38.000 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: That was blood.

00:03:38.000 --> 00:03:40.750 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't know he
was ill or anything.

00:03:40.750 --> 00:03:43.150 align:middle line:84%
I did not know he
was having a surgery.

00:03:43.150 --> 00:03:47.590 align:middle line:84%
And then what happened is that,
again, I come back next morning

00:03:47.590 --> 00:03:48.580 align:middle line:90%
and continue.

00:03:48.580 --> 00:03:53.210 align:middle line:84%
But when my aunt came back
from that trip and I told her,

00:03:53.210 --> 00:03:57.140 align:middle line:84%
look, how is it possible
you should be just traveling

00:03:57.140 --> 00:03:57.940 align:middle line:90%
for tourism?

00:03:57.940 --> 00:04:01.970 align:middle line:84%
And I saw uncle Geno, that
was his name, in this place,

00:04:01.970 --> 00:04:02.770 align:middle line:90%
in this condition.

00:04:02.770 --> 00:04:04.330 align:middle line:90%
And I described the tube.

00:04:04.330 --> 00:04:05.690 align:middle line:90%
And she was so--

00:04:05.690 --> 00:04:06.490 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: In shock.

00:04:06.490 --> 00:04:07.290 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: In shock.

00:04:07.290 --> 00:04:08.890 align:middle line:84%
She was in shock
because we imagined

00:04:08.890 --> 00:04:11.650 align:middle line:84%
nobody studied anything
like this in my family.

00:04:11.650 --> 00:04:13.810 align:middle line:84%
So it was pretty much just
having the experience--

00:04:13.810 --> 00:04:16.143 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: And you were accurate
with what you described.

00:04:16.143 --> 00:04:21.100 align:middle line:10%
>>NANCI: It was on the spot,
and I overheard her talking

00:04:21.100 --> 00:04:25.180 align:middle line:10%
to my mother later on not
knowing I was close by.

00:04:25.180 --> 00:04:27.460 align:middle line:84%
How is it possible
that she saw that?

00:04:27.460 --> 00:04:28.360 align:middle line:90%
It couldn't be.

00:04:28.360 --> 00:04:30.640 align:middle line:84%
But then they don't
talk about this anymore

00:04:30.640 --> 00:04:32.388 align:middle line:84%
because this
produces fear maybe.

00:04:32.388 --> 00:04:33.430 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: They're scared.

00:04:33.430 --> 00:04:36.310 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: But in my
mind, I think if it's

00:04:36.310 --> 00:04:38.420 align:middle line:84%
possible to have an
experience like this,

00:04:38.420 --> 00:04:39.970 align:middle line:90%
which I have had several.

00:04:39.970 --> 00:04:42.880 align:middle line:84%
But to me, that is
very remarkable,

00:04:42.880 --> 00:04:45.790 align:middle line:84%
because I couldn't
have imagined that.

00:04:45.790 --> 00:04:46.840 align:middle line:90%
No way.

00:04:46.840 --> 00:04:50.140 align:middle line:84%
I am from the time
when TV sets, I

00:04:50.140 --> 00:04:52.270 align:middle line:84%
would have to watch TV
on the neighbor's house,

00:04:52.270 --> 00:04:57.400 align:middle line:84%
and it was all full of
different marks and signals.

00:04:57.400 --> 00:04:59.020 align:middle line:84%
And you have to
adjust the antenna.

00:04:59.020 --> 00:05:00.820 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: We call
that video noise.

00:05:00.820 --> 00:05:01.695 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Video noise.

00:05:01.695 --> 00:05:02.495 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:05:02.495 --> 00:05:03.700 align:middle line:90%
It was still full of noise.

00:05:03.700 --> 00:05:08.240 align:middle line:84%
So I've never seen even
a hospital in my life.

00:05:08.240 --> 00:05:09.700 align:middle line:90%
So that was so accurate.

00:05:09.700 --> 00:05:13.780 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, we should
have serious studies.

00:05:13.780 --> 00:05:16.240 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to understand
more because I

00:05:16.240 --> 00:05:19.180 align:middle line:90%
am eager to know whys and hows.

00:05:19.180 --> 00:05:21.070 align:middle line:84%
And what is it that
we are doing here?

00:05:21.070 --> 00:05:23.185 align:middle line:90%
And how do we grow from inside?

00:05:23.185 --> 00:05:25.360 align:middle line:90%
How do I become a better person?

00:05:25.360 --> 00:05:27.190 align:middle line:90%
That has always been in my mind.

00:05:27.190 --> 00:05:29.200 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Were these
OBEs, these out-of-body

00:05:29.200 --> 00:05:32.230 align:middle line:84%
experiences happening
often to you?

00:05:32.230 --> 00:05:35.560 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: At that age, yes,
very often and very easily.

00:05:35.560 --> 00:05:38.720 align:middle line:84%
I did not know so much how
to take advantage of them.

00:05:38.720 --> 00:05:41.788 align:middle line:84%
I would just experience the
sensation and float around.

00:05:41.788 --> 00:05:44.080 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: And they just
happen, because you didn't even

00:05:44.080 --> 00:05:45.200 align:middle line:90%
know how to do it.

00:05:45.200 --> 00:05:46.960 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: I didn't even
know how to do it,

00:05:46.960 --> 00:05:50.530 align:middle line:84%
not knowing that it was an
important phenomenon happened

00:05:50.530 --> 00:05:51.580 align:middle line:90%
very easily.

00:05:51.580 --> 00:05:54.956 align:middle line:84%
Nowadays not so easily
anymore, unfortunately.

00:05:54.956 --> 00:05:56.230 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Now you know.

00:05:56.230 --> 00:06:00.250 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: Now that I want them,
they are not there so easily.

00:06:00.250 --> 00:06:04.390 align:middle line:84%
But yes, that was very
remarkable, I guess.

00:06:04.390 --> 00:06:07.180 align:middle line:84%
And that led me to
become a researcher

00:06:07.180 --> 00:06:08.650 align:middle line:90%
of the out-of-body experience.

00:06:08.650 --> 00:06:13.000 align:middle line:84%
But not only I
wanted to understand

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:16.000 align:middle line:84%
what is the bridge
between the physical world

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:17.650 align:middle line:90%
and the non-physical world?

00:06:17.650 --> 00:06:19.810 align:middle line:84%
And how can so many
phenomena be explained?

00:06:19.810 --> 00:06:21.477 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: How were
you able to determine

00:06:21.477 --> 00:06:24.730 align:middle line:84%
the difference between the
physical and the spiritual?

00:06:24.730 --> 00:06:27.370 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: That is the one
billion dollar question,

00:06:27.370 --> 00:06:30.040 align:middle line:84%
because we can see that
from different perspectives.

00:06:30.040 --> 00:06:35.020 align:middle line:84%
From the personal perspective,
how do we know what is a dream?

00:06:35.020 --> 00:06:36.230 align:middle line:90%
What's imagination?

00:06:36.230 --> 00:06:37.360 align:middle line:90%
And what's real?

00:06:37.360 --> 00:06:41.650 align:middle line:84%
And that is a very fair question
that not always the person

00:06:41.650 --> 00:06:44.080 align:middle line:84%
who is experiencing
the phenomenon knows.

00:06:44.080 --> 00:06:46.570 align:middle line:84%
But in some cases,
it's so vivid, so

00:06:46.570 --> 00:06:50.890 align:middle line:84%
clear that it's more vivid
than this world here.

00:06:50.890 --> 00:06:55.780 align:middle line:84%
And some people experience these
phenomena in a very natural

00:06:55.780 --> 00:06:57.290 align:middle line:90%
spontaneous way.

00:06:57.290 --> 00:07:01.210 align:middle line:84%
So there are some
cases as remarkable

00:07:01.210 --> 00:07:04.090 align:middle line:90%
and confirmed as the one I said.

00:07:04.090 --> 00:07:06.040 align:middle line:90%
But others very spontaneous one.

00:07:06.040 --> 00:07:08.800 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Nanci, how do you
explain the perceptions that

00:07:08.800 --> 00:07:10.450 align:middle line:90%
go beyond the physical senses?

00:07:10.450 --> 00:07:12.850 align:middle line:90%
What is this all about?

00:07:12.850 --> 00:07:17.290 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: From all of my studies,
and that's a major area for me,

00:07:17.290 --> 00:07:21.730 align:middle line:84%
is to understand this bridge
between our physical senses

00:07:21.730 --> 00:07:24.010 align:middle line:90%
and physical body and the brain.

00:07:24.010 --> 00:07:27.940 align:middle line:84%
And these non-local
perceptions and what people

00:07:27.940 --> 00:07:29.270 align:middle line:90%
call astral body.

00:07:29.270 --> 00:07:30.430 align:middle line:90%
How do they bridge?

00:07:30.430 --> 00:07:33.822 align:middle line:84%
How is it possible that someone
has an experience that--

00:07:33.822 --> 00:07:34.780 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Like you had.

00:07:34.780 --> 00:07:37.600 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: Like I had, like
an out-of-body experience,

00:07:37.600 --> 00:07:41.260 align:middle line:84%
that basically we are
not inside the brain,

00:07:41.260 --> 00:07:45.400 align:middle line:84%
we are not using the brain,
and we can transfer information

00:07:45.400 --> 00:07:48.740 align:middle line:84%
from the memories that we have
from that experience to here.

00:07:48.740 --> 00:07:50.560 align:middle line:84%
So there is some
sort of energy that

00:07:50.560 --> 00:07:54.070 align:middle line:84%
creates this bridge
that seems to be

00:07:54.070 --> 00:07:58.150 align:middle line:84%
key in all of these
different psychic phenomena.

00:07:58.150 --> 00:08:00.160 align:middle line:84%
One interesting
thing, George, is

00:08:00.160 --> 00:08:05.890 align:middle line:84%
that so many people are somehow
sensitive to these energy.

00:08:05.890 --> 00:08:08.740 align:middle line:84%
People call it different
names, aura chakras.

00:08:08.740 --> 00:08:12.430 align:middle line:84%
I just like to call it energetic
interface or energy body,

00:08:12.430 --> 00:08:13.990 align:middle line:90%
to be simpler.

00:08:13.990 --> 00:08:17.410 align:middle line:84%
The thing is that when we
study about physical body,

00:08:17.410 --> 00:08:20.360 align:middle line:84%
we can study our physiology
and know how it works.

00:08:20.360 --> 00:08:22.000 align:middle line:90%
And have explanations.

00:08:22.000 --> 00:08:24.572 align:middle line:84%
But your physiology,
let's say, is

00:08:24.572 --> 00:08:25.780 align:middle line:90%
slightly different than mine.

00:08:25.780 --> 00:08:28.960 align:middle line:84%
What you can eat will be
different than what I can eat.

00:08:28.960 --> 00:08:30.850 align:middle line:84%
What is good for
you is different

00:08:30.850 --> 00:08:34.510 align:middle line:84%
when we do an exercise,
physical exercise, some of us,

00:08:34.510 --> 00:08:35.840 align:middle line:90%
we have more flexibility.

00:08:35.840 --> 00:08:39.039 align:middle line:84%
Some of us we have to take care
with some aspect of our let's

00:08:39.039 --> 00:08:41.039 align:middle line:90%
say spine.

00:08:41.039 --> 00:08:44.580 align:middle line:84%
We should have the same
type of knowledge in regards

00:08:44.580 --> 00:08:45.510 align:middle line:90%
to the energy body.

00:08:45.510 --> 00:08:48.030 align:middle line:90%
But that is so neglected.

00:08:48.030 --> 00:08:50.460 align:middle line:84%
And one big effort
that I have been doing

00:08:50.460 --> 00:08:53.610 align:middle line:84%
is how to compile
cases and information

00:08:53.610 --> 00:08:57.180 align:middle line:84%
and logical explanations
that would at least give us

00:08:57.180 --> 00:09:00.570 align:middle line:84%
some light into what is
an energy perception?

00:09:00.570 --> 00:09:04.650 align:middle line:84%
What is it that we can pick
out of intuition or telepathy?

00:09:04.650 --> 00:09:07.950 align:middle line:84%
What is it that happens when we
are close to someone, and all

00:09:07.950 --> 00:09:11.340 align:middle line:84%
of a sudden, we have an idea
that is absolutely related

00:09:11.340 --> 00:09:14.130 align:middle line:84%
to that person, but we never
thought of that before?

00:09:14.130 --> 00:09:15.960 align:middle line:90%
What explains that?

00:09:15.960 --> 00:09:18.900 align:middle line:84%
And this sort of thing,
it's just because it's

00:09:18.900 --> 00:09:22.060 align:middle line:84%
so hard to explain, and it
is, and so hard to research,

00:09:22.060 --> 00:09:25.290 align:middle line:84%
I think it is just left
aside and just dismissed

00:09:25.290 --> 00:09:29.250 align:middle line:84%
as a general name like
intuition, gut feeling.

00:09:29.250 --> 00:09:32.610 align:middle line:90%
And I'd like to be more--

00:09:32.610 --> 00:09:36.090 align:middle line:84%
I'd say logical, it's not
the word I'm looking for.

00:09:36.090 --> 00:09:38.880 align:middle line:84%
I'd like to be more
technical about that.

00:09:38.880 --> 00:09:40.050 align:middle line:90%
How it happened.

00:09:40.050 --> 00:09:41.800 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: When I
was 11 years old,

00:09:41.800 --> 00:09:46.100 align:middle line:84%
I woke up in bed
looking down at my body.

00:09:46.100 --> 00:09:47.630 align:middle line:90%
And I'm awake.

00:09:47.630 --> 00:09:49.820 align:middle line:84%
And I'm saying this
is not a dream.

00:09:49.820 --> 00:09:50.960 align:middle line:90%
What is this?

00:09:50.960 --> 00:09:54.740 align:middle line:84%
At that moment, it slammed
me back into the body.

00:09:54.740 --> 00:09:59.340 align:middle line:84%
And I woke up again jarred
and said, what happened to me?

00:09:59.340 --> 00:10:02.480 align:middle line:84%
So I went to the
bookstore and I was

00:10:02.480 --> 00:10:05.420 align:middle line:84%
walking around looking
for something that would

00:10:05.420 --> 00:10:07.370 align:middle line:90%
explain what happened to me?

00:10:07.370 --> 00:10:09.560 align:middle line:84%
And I found a book
called "Projections

00:10:09.560 --> 00:10:13.750 align:middle line:84%
of the Astral Body" by Hereward
Carrington and Sylvan Muldoon.

00:10:13.750 --> 00:10:14.750 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: It's wonderful.

00:10:14.750 --> 00:10:18.530 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: And they had a picture
on the book of an astral body

00:10:18.530 --> 00:10:20.510 align:middle line:90%
floating over a physical body.

00:10:20.510 --> 00:10:23.120 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking at
this, 11 years old.

00:10:23.120 --> 00:10:24.780 align:middle line:90%
That's what happened to me.

00:10:24.780 --> 00:10:26.420 align:middle line:84%
And that was one
of the reasons why

00:10:26.420 --> 00:10:28.850 align:middle line:84%
I decided to get
into broadcasting

00:10:28.850 --> 00:10:31.250 align:middle line:90%
to unravel these stories.

00:10:31.250 --> 00:10:33.060 align:middle line:90%
It was an amazing thing.

00:10:33.060 --> 00:10:36.260 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: It's a great work
that you do, a great service,

00:10:36.260 --> 00:10:39.710 align:middle line:84%
because we need to bring
more awareness about this.

00:10:39.710 --> 00:10:44.090 align:middle line:84%
And we need to give a
platform for serious studies.

00:10:44.090 --> 00:10:47.340 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Theoretical scientists
and biologist Stuart Kauffman

00:10:47.340 --> 00:10:51.020 align:middle line:84%
describes a very profound
vision he had of a future event.

00:10:51.020 --> 00:10:51.820 align:middle line:90%
[VIDEO PLAYBACK]

00:10:51.820 --> 00:10:55.980 align:middle line:84%
- And when she was 13, we
were living in Philadelphia.

00:10:55.980 --> 00:10:58.530 align:middle line:84%
And I picked Merit up
at her boyfriend's.

00:10:58.530 --> 00:11:00.610 align:middle line:84%
I did not want Merit at
13 to have a boyfriend.

00:11:00.610 --> 00:11:01.410 align:middle line:90%
- I see.

00:11:01.410 --> 00:11:04.180 align:middle line:84%
- Merit wasn't going to
listen to her father.

00:11:04.180 --> 00:11:06.840 align:middle line:84%
And she said, daddy, I'm going
to walk home from Alex's house.

00:11:06.840 --> 00:11:08.940 align:middle line:84%
Well, any father of a
13-year-old daughter

00:11:08.940 --> 00:11:11.498 align:middle line:84%
would be worried,
because I thought

00:11:11.498 --> 00:11:12.540 align:middle line:90%
it was about three miles.

00:11:12.540 --> 00:11:13.950 align:middle line:90%
It was actually five miles.

00:11:13.950 --> 00:11:15.240 align:middle line:90%
And I picked her up.

00:11:15.240 --> 00:11:17.360 align:middle line:84%
And we pulled out
of Alex's driveway.

00:11:17.360 --> 00:11:19.890 align:middle line:84%
And then we pulled on to
a slightly larger street.

00:11:19.890 --> 00:11:23.370 align:middle line:84%
And I was absolutely
dumbstruck with terror

00:11:23.370 --> 00:11:25.200 align:middle line:90%
as we drove past a tree.

00:11:25.200 --> 00:11:30.600 align:middle line:10%
And I saw Merit walking
down the middle of the lane

00:11:30.600 --> 00:11:34.980 align:middle line:10%
and hit from behind
by a car and crushed.

00:11:34.980 --> 00:11:36.870 align:middle line:90%
And I was terrified.

00:11:36.870 --> 00:11:41.070 align:middle line:84%
And I said, Merit, don't ever
walk home from Alex's house.

00:11:41.070 --> 00:11:43.350 align:middle line:10%
You call mom or me day or night.

00:11:43.350 --> 00:11:44.310 align:middle line:90%
And Merit was silent.

00:11:44.310 --> 00:11:46.530 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, I'm
having an argument

00:11:46.530 --> 00:11:49.200 align:middle line:90%
with my teenage daughter.

00:11:49.200 --> 00:11:50.850 align:middle line:84%
I think I'm going
to lose this one.

00:11:50.850 --> 00:11:52.410 align:middle line:84%
She's entering a
dangerous period.

00:11:52.410 --> 00:11:54.425 align:middle line:84%
If she makes it to
16, she'll be fine.

00:11:54.425 --> 00:11:55.800 align:middle line:84%
Then she said,
don't worry daddy.

00:11:55.800 --> 00:11:58.990 align:middle line:84%
If I walk home, I'll call you
from the Roy Rogers up here.

00:11:58.990 --> 00:12:01.120 align:middle line:84%
I said, well, that's
an OK compromise.

00:12:01.120 --> 00:12:03.090 align:middle line:84%
But a month later, Merit
was over at Alex's.

00:12:03.090 --> 00:12:06.450 align:middle line:90%


00:12:06.450 --> 00:12:08.910 align:middle line:90%
He broke up with her.

00:12:08.910 --> 00:12:12.930 align:middle line:84%
And Merit walked out and
she did almost what I said.

00:12:12.930 --> 00:12:15.240 align:middle line:84%
She was walking down
the middle of the lane

00:12:15.240 --> 00:12:17.850 align:middle line:84%
and was hit from
behind by a car.

00:12:17.850 --> 00:12:20.970 align:middle line:84%
Not quite, but approximately,
and killed on the very spot

00:12:20.970 --> 00:12:22.620 align:middle line:90%
where I saw it happening.

00:12:22.620 --> 00:12:23.970 align:middle line:90%
And I haven't gotten over it.

00:12:23.970 --> 00:12:26.080 align:middle line:90%
It was 32 years ago.

00:12:26.080 --> 00:12:32.160 align:middle line:84%
So I can account for being
worried that any parent would.

00:12:32.160 --> 00:12:35.490 align:middle line:84%
But I can't account for the
specificity of that image,

00:12:35.490 --> 00:12:38.160 align:middle line:84%
nor can I account for the
fact that the next morning,

00:12:38.160 --> 00:12:40.350 align:middle line:84%
I called a woman
named Linda Haley.

00:12:40.350 --> 00:12:41.850 align:middle line:84%
I've known Linda
since she was born.

00:12:41.850 --> 00:12:43.170 align:middle line:90%
And I was three.

00:12:43.170 --> 00:12:45.960 align:middle line:84%
And I told her that
Merit had died.

00:12:45.960 --> 00:12:50.070 align:middle line:84%
My God, last night I had a
dream that you were crushed

00:12:50.070 --> 00:12:54.480 align:middle line:84%
and crumpled in grief on
your dining room floor.

00:12:54.480 --> 00:12:57.420 align:middle line:84%
And Liz, my wife, was
behind me holding me.

00:12:57.420 --> 00:12:58.540 align:middle line:90%
And then it wasn't me.

00:12:58.540 --> 00:13:00.000 align:middle line:84%
She said I thought
you were dying.

00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:01.498 align:middle line:84%
Why didn't Linda
have that dream?

00:13:01.498 --> 00:13:03.540 align:middle line:84%
We hadn't talked to one
another for eight months.

00:13:03.540 --> 00:13:06.360 align:middle line:90%
And she was 2,000 miles away.

00:13:06.360 --> 00:13:07.440 align:middle line:90%
Well, OK.

00:13:07.440 --> 00:13:09.300 align:middle line:90%
These things happen sometimes.

00:13:09.300 --> 00:13:10.260 align:middle line:90%
I don't think so.

00:13:10.260 --> 00:13:11.070 align:middle line:90%
- Yes.

00:13:11.070 --> 00:13:12.720 align:middle line:90%
Too much to be a coincidence.

00:13:12.720 --> 00:13:13.520 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:13:13.520 --> 00:13:15.120 align:middle line:90%
- It's real.

00:13:15.120 --> 00:13:20.910 align:middle line:84%
So to jump ahead, I think
telepathy is possible.

00:13:20.910 --> 00:13:24.150 align:middle line:84%
If the mind body system is
quantum classical, which

00:13:24.150 --> 00:13:27.030 align:middle line:84%
I think it probably is,
then via non-locality,

00:13:27.030 --> 00:13:30.630 align:middle line:84%
which we can get to, I think
that something telepathic

00:13:30.630 --> 00:13:31.470 align:middle line:90%
can happen.

00:13:31.470 --> 00:13:33.960 align:middle line:84%
And it's going to be very
evanescent because it

00:13:33.960 --> 00:13:35.310 align:middle line:90%
relies on entanglement.

00:13:35.310 --> 00:13:37.440 align:middle line:84%
And entanglement
is very evanescent.

00:13:37.440 --> 00:13:40.470 align:middle line:84%
So getting reliable stable
data is going to be very hard.

00:13:40.470 --> 00:13:41.860 align:middle line:90%
But we don't take it seriously.

00:13:41.860 --> 00:13:42.840 align:middle line:84%
I think we're just
being stubborn.

00:13:42.840 --> 00:13:43.800 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:13:43.800 --> 00:13:45.450 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: It's quite an
experience he went through.

00:13:45.450 --> 00:13:45.960 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Yes.

00:13:45.960 --> 00:13:46.760 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

00:13:46.760 --> 00:13:50.495 align:middle line:84%
And he candidly shared that I
think it was very important.

00:13:50.495 --> 00:13:51.870 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: When he
was telling you

00:13:51.870 --> 00:13:53.490 align:middle line:90%
that, what were you thinking?

00:13:53.490 --> 00:13:55.620 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: I was
thinking how brave

00:13:55.620 --> 00:13:56.820 align:middle line:90%
he was to go through that.

00:13:56.820 --> 00:14:00.150 align:middle line:90%
How painful that must have been.

00:14:00.150 --> 00:14:05.040 align:middle line:84%
And thinking how amazing
that this sort of thing

00:14:05.040 --> 00:14:10.020 align:middle line:84%
happened to those that never had
an experience, never studied,

00:14:10.020 --> 00:14:13.200 align:middle line:84%
and it's much more common
than we would think.

00:14:13.200 --> 00:14:15.120 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Have you
ever been afraid of any

00:14:15.120 --> 00:14:17.130 align:middle line:90%
of these experiences?

00:14:17.130 --> 00:14:18.360 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Yes, I have.

00:14:18.360 --> 00:14:19.360 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: What happened?

00:14:19.360 --> 00:14:21.300 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: I have been
afraid a few times.

00:14:21.300 --> 00:14:22.383 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: What scares you?

00:14:22.383 --> 00:14:24.930 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: But especially,
like some entities

00:14:24.930 --> 00:14:28.830 align:middle line:84%
around that were not nice, not
in my out-of-body experience.

00:14:28.830 --> 00:14:30.570 align:middle line:84%
My out-of-body
experience, I guess

00:14:30.570 --> 00:14:32.880 align:middle line:90%
they were always kind of nice.

00:14:32.880 --> 00:14:35.590 align:middle line:84%
Some of them were
vivid than others.

00:14:35.590 --> 00:14:38.910 align:middle line:84%
But when I was
around 13, George,

00:14:38.910 --> 00:14:41.310 align:middle line:84%
we moved from that
small city that

00:14:41.310 --> 00:14:44.670 align:middle line:84%
was very peaceful and
clean to another city

00:14:44.670 --> 00:14:46.670 align:middle line:90%
that I didn't fancy very much.

00:14:46.670 --> 00:14:50.840 align:middle line:84%
But the point was that we had to
move from one house to another

00:14:50.840 --> 00:14:52.280 align:middle line:90%
until we find our place.

00:14:52.280 --> 00:14:55.100 align:middle line:84%
In one of the
houses that we were,

00:14:55.100 --> 00:14:58.520 align:middle line:84%
I started sensing there was
some sort of ghosts there,

00:14:58.520 --> 00:15:00.170 align:middle line:90%
I'm going to put it this way.

00:15:00.170 --> 00:15:02.610 align:middle line:90%
And I was afraid.

00:15:02.610 --> 00:15:05.450 align:middle line:84%
I was afraid because
I would wake up

00:15:05.450 --> 00:15:09.110 align:middle line:84%
every night in the middle
of the night sensing

00:15:09.110 --> 00:15:10.040 align:middle line:90%
that they were very--

00:15:10.040 --> 00:15:10.873 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Petrified.

00:15:10.873 --> 00:15:11.780 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Petrified.

00:15:11.780 --> 00:15:13.670 align:middle line:90%
That is exactly the word.

00:15:13.670 --> 00:15:14.570 align:middle line:90%
Petrified.

00:15:14.570 --> 00:15:16.560 align:middle line:90%
I couldn't move.

00:15:16.560 --> 00:15:18.170 align:middle line:90%
I was in terror.

00:15:18.170 --> 00:15:22.850 align:middle line:84%
And that would last a long
time, one hour, two hours.

00:15:22.850 --> 00:15:24.350 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Did you
tell your parents?

00:15:24.350 --> 00:15:26.398 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: I did not
know how to say.

00:15:26.398 --> 00:15:28.190 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: So you kept
this within yourself?

00:15:28.190 --> 00:15:30.620 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: I kept-- I would
tell my mother I'm afraid.

00:15:30.620 --> 00:15:32.630 align:middle line:90%
She didn't know afraid of what.

00:15:32.630 --> 00:15:36.680 align:middle line:84%
And after some time, I started
becoming even shyer than I was,

00:15:36.680 --> 00:15:37.760 align:middle line:90%
more and more shy.

00:15:37.760 --> 00:15:38.560 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: You?

00:15:38.560 --> 00:15:39.770 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Yes.

00:15:39.770 --> 00:15:40.920 align:middle line:90%
Believe it or not.

00:15:40.920 --> 00:15:44.720 align:middle line:84%
This sort of sensitivity in
childhood made me very shy,

00:15:44.720 --> 00:15:48.320 align:middle line:84%
because I would sense people's
energy in different places.

00:15:48.320 --> 00:15:52.940 align:middle line:84%
And I don't know to
me it was very hard.

00:15:52.940 --> 00:15:56.460 align:middle line:84%
But then later, of course, I
learned how to work with energy

00:15:56.460 --> 00:15:57.720 align:middle line:90%
and balance that.

00:15:57.720 --> 00:16:02.590 align:middle line:84%
But those experiences, they
were very, very impactful,

00:16:02.590 --> 00:16:03.430 align:middle line:90%
traumatic.

00:16:03.430 --> 00:16:08.260 align:middle line:84%
Even took me a long time
to let go of that fear.

00:16:08.260 --> 00:16:12.820 align:middle line:84%
And I'd say that they
left deep marks in myself.

00:16:12.820 --> 00:16:13.870 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Scarred you?

00:16:13.870 --> 00:16:15.670 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: Scarred
me because there

00:16:15.670 --> 00:16:18.220 align:middle line:84%
were cases in which I was
about to leave the body,

00:16:18.220 --> 00:16:20.730 align:middle line:90%
and I would react automatically.

00:16:20.730 --> 00:16:24.090 align:middle line:84%
Although I have had so many
out-of-body experiences before,

00:16:24.090 --> 00:16:27.990 align:middle line:84%
but sensing the
non-physical world

00:16:27.990 --> 00:16:33.720 align:middle line:84%
and that so many people and
entities bullying me only

00:16:33.720 --> 00:16:39.990 align:middle line:84%
was not threatening me in any
direct way that today I know.

00:16:39.990 --> 00:16:44.190 align:middle line:84%
It's just having fun of
making a child scared.

00:16:44.190 --> 00:16:46.960 align:middle line:84%
And so many children
go through it.

00:16:46.960 --> 00:16:50.340 align:middle line:84%
But when I sense
that and sometimes I

00:16:50.340 --> 00:16:53.760 align:middle line:84%
would leave my body,
it's not that I

00:16:53.760 --> 00:16:55.740 align:middle line:84%
didn't want to
leave the body, it's

00:16:55.740 --> 00:16:58.980 align:middle line:84%
just that it was an automatic
reaction, pretty much

00:16:58.980 --> 00:17:01.710 align:middle line:90%
like post-traumatic syndrome.

00:17:01.710 --> 00:17:05.010 align:middle line:84%
And then I would
block the experience.

00:17:05.010 --> 00:17:06.990 align:middle line:90%
And eventually, I overcame that.

00:17:06.990 --> 00:17:09.030 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Muldoon
and Carrington wrote

00:17:09.030 --> 00:17:12.300 align:middle line:84%
that there are levels in
the astral plane you do not

00:17:12.300 --> 00:17:14.310 align:middle line:90%
want to stop off at.

00:17:14.310 --> 00:17:15.900 align:middle line:90%
Have you encountered that?

00:17:15.900 --> 00:17:17.040 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: I have.

00:17:17.040 --> 00:17:17.950 align:middle line:90%
I have.

00:17:17.950 --> 00:17:22.109 align:middle line:84%
And I found in my
experience that when

00:17:22.109 --> 00:17:27.119 align:middle line:84%
you go into the real spirit
world, so I say spirituality

00:17:27.119 --> 00:17:29.250 align:middle line:84%
is about being a
spirit out there.

00:17:29.250 --> 00:17:31.330 align:middle line:84%
We are spirits in
the physical body.

00:17:31.330 --> 00:17:34.740 align:middle line:84%
So the actual spirituality
is us getting closer

00:17:34.740 --> 00:17:39.270 align:middle line:84%
to our true nature and seeing
what is the spirit world,

00:17:39.270 --> 00:17:40.830 align:middle line:90%
the non-physical world.

00:17:40.830 --> 00:17:44.520 align:middle line:84%
And I have been to
places that it gave me

00:17:44.520 --> 00:17:49.860 align:middle line:90%
a frame of how low we can be.

00:17:49.860 --> 00:17:51.780 align:middle line:90%
We, I mean beings--

00:17:51.780 --> 00:17:52.810 align:middle line:90%
human beings.

00:17:52.810 --> 00:17:56.440 align:middle line:84%
I have been places that I
saw people that were really

00:17:56.440 --> 00:17:58.630 align:middle line:90%
not very good condition.

00:17:58.630 --> 00:18:01.780 align:middle line:84%
If I may describe, then you
see if you keep it or not.

00:18:01.780 --> 00:18:04.926 align:middle line:84%
But pretty much a bit
like what we see in "What

00:18:04.926 --> 00:18:06.730 align:middle line:90%
Dreams May Come" movie.

00:18:06.730 --> 00:18:08.070 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: With Robin Williams.

00:18:08.070 --> 00:18:08.870 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Yes.

00:18:08.870 --> 00:18:11.270 align:middle line:90%
Some places were like that.

00:18:11.270 --> 00:18:15.100 align:middle line:84%
But when I am there, I'm
never afraid because I

00:18:15.100 --> 00:18:17.230 align:middle line:90%
am in that reality.

00:18:17.230 --> 00:18:20.290 align:middle line:84%
But I also have been to
places and encountered

00:18:20.290 --> 00:18:25.450 align:middle line:84%
people that are so much beyond
any description we hear here

00:18:25.450 --> 00:18:29.440 align:middle line:84%
in our world of an advanced
person, an enlightened person.

00:18:29.440 --> 00:18:33.070 align:middle line:84%
And I say goodness, we
should aim at becoming better

00:18:33.070 --> 00:18:37.000 align:middle line:84%
because there is so
much ahead of us,

00:18:37.000 --> 00:18:42.670 align:middle line:84%
because we can see this huge
gap, this huge difference

00:18:42.670 --> 00:18:47.140 align:middle line:84%
from the condition, the internal
condition of some individuals

00:18:47.140 --> 00:18:51.880 align:middle line:84%
and of others who have already
developed some, perhaps

00:18:51.880 --> 00:18:54.370 align:middle line:84%
the skills I would
say or attributes

00:18:54.370 --> 00:18:56.950 align:middle line:90%
that we are still learning them.

00:18:56.950 --> 00:18:58.388 align:middle line:90%
That's what I would say.

00:18:58.388 --> 00:19:00.180 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: What do you
think, though, Nanci,

00:19:00.180 --> 00:19:03.070 align:middle line:90%
an out-of-body experience is?

00:19:03.070 --> 00:19:04.810 align:middle line:90%
Why do we do these?

00:19:04.810 --> 00:19:07.090 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: I think that
is a natural phenomenon.

00:19:07.090 --> 00:19:13.360 align:middle line:84%
Very natural that,
unfortunately, society in a way

00:19:13.360 --> 00:19:14.410 align:middle line:90%
represses it.

00:19:14.410 --> 00:19:15.812 align:middle line:90%
Nowadays it is a bit better.

00:19:15.812 --> 00:19:17.270 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: They
don't understand it.

00:19:17.270 --> 00:19:18.562 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: They don't understand.

00:19:18.562 --> 00:19:19.990 align:middle line:90%
They are afraid of it, right?

00:19:19.990 --> 00:19:21.590 align:middle line:90%
And fear plays a big role.

00:19:21.590 --> 00:19:22.390 align:middle line:90%
Some are.

00:19:22.390 --> 00:19:24.100 align:middle line:84%
But I mean, society
in general, when

00:19:24.100 --> 00:19:26.920 align:middle line:84%
we think of the
large population,

00:19:26.920 --> 00:19:31.360 align:middle line:84%
thankfully nowadays we
have shows like yours

00:19:31.360 --> 00:19:34.180 align:middle line:84%
and so many people bring
information about this

00:19:34.180 --> 00:19:39.490 align:middle line:84%
in the internet basically, which
is there for everyone, which

00:19:39.490 --> 00:19:43.570 align:middle line:84%
is a great thing because
it's more accessible,

00:19:43.570 --> 00:19:46.990 align:middle line:84%
but also a dangerous thing,
because we do not have

00:19:46.990 --> 00:19:49.960 align:middle line:90%
an FDA of the spirituality.

