00:22:01.970 --> 00:22:09.800 align:middle line:84%
- The turning experience for me
happened when I was 48 or 49.

00:22:09.800 --> 00:22:13.250 align:middle line:84%
And for a number
of years before, I

00:22:13.250 --> 00:22:18.110 align:middle line:84%
was interested in understanding
the nature of consciousness.

00:22:18.110 --> 00:22:25.720 align:middle line:84%
And I wanted to make a conscious
computer, or not to make,

00:22:25.720 --> 00:22:29.390 align:middle line:84%
but find out if it was possible
to make a conscious computer.

00:22:29.390 --> 00:22:31.970 align:middle line:84%
And so I was exploring
on my spare time

00:22:31.970 --> 00:22:36.490 align:middle line:84%
that idea, thinking that
if in fact consciousness

00:22:36.490 --> 00:22:40.330 align:middle line:84%
is an epiphenomenon or
is an emergent property

00:22:40.330 --> 00:22:43.030 align:middle line:84%
of a complex system,
well, then a computer

00:22:43.030 --> 00:22:46.960 align:middle line:90%
should be able to be conscious.

00:22:46.960 --> 00:22:50.830 align:middle line:84%
So the more I thought, the
more impossible it appeared.

00:22:50.830 --> 00:22:55.828 align:middle line:84%
And I was kind of also
somewhat frustrated.

00:22:55.828 --> 00:22:59.140 align:middle line:84%
In those days, I was a
materialist, a physicalist.

00:22:59.140 --> 00:23:02.530 align:middle line:84%
I thought that the
science had the answers,

00:23:02.530 --> 00:23:06.250 align:middle line:84%
and that the world
is made of matter.

00:23:06.250 --> 00:23:07.330 align:middle line:90%
And that's the end of it.

00:23:07.330 --> 00:23:13.060 align:middle line:84%
And consciousness is
probably an epiphenomenon.

00:23:13.060 --> 00:23:15.550 align:middle line:90%
And so-- but I was interested.

00:23:15.550 --> 00:23:16.970 align:middle line:90%
I was not giving up.

00:23:16.970 --> 00:23:24.300 align:middle line:84%
And at some level, I think
I pray to understand.

00:23:24.300 --> 00:23:29.060 align:middle line:84%
And so I ended up having
a extraordinary experience

00:23:29.060 --> 00:23:29.920 align:middle line:90%
of consciousness.

00:23:29.920 --> 00:23:33.750 align:middle line:84%
What generally
would be classified

00:23:33.750 --> 00:23:35.520 align:middle line:90%
as a mystical experience.

00:23:35.520 --> 00:23:40.830 align:middle line:84%
But I don't want to put names
because it doesn't really help.

00:23:40.830 --> 00:23:46.320 align:middle line:84%
Where fundamentally I
experienced myself as love,

00:23:46.320 --> 00:23:49.440 align:middle line:90%
and I was love.

00:23:49.440 --> 00:23:54.120 align:middle line:84%
And I was the universe,
which was made of love.

00:23:54.120 --> 00:23:57.540 align:middle line:84%
But I was also the observer
of the universe that

00:23:57.540 --> 00:24:00.300 align:middle line:90%
is me that is made of love.

00:24:00.300 --> 00:24:05.760 align:middle line:84%
So this experience changes
all the fundamental paradigms

00:24:05.760 --> 00:24:11.490 align:middle line:84%
of physicality that you have,
because in ordinary experience,

00:24:11.490 --> 00:24:14.010 align:middle line:84%
I am a body existing
inside a world ,

00:24:14.010 --> 00:24:16.650 align:middle line:84%
and the world is objective, and
I interact with other bodies,

00:24:16.650 --> 00:24:19.600 align:middle line:84%
and I'm separate from the
world, and all of that.

00:24:19.600 --> 00:24:22.560 align:middle line:84%
But in this experience,
I am the world.

00:24:22.560 --> 00:24:25.290 align:middle line:84%
But I'm also the
observer of the world.

00:24:25.290 --> 00:24:28.000 align:middle line:84%
And the world is
not made of things.

00:24:28.000 --> 00:24:29.790 align:middle line:90%
It's made of love.

00:24:29.790 --> 00:24:33.820 align:middle line:84%
So that was about 20
seconds to a minute.

00:24:33.820 --> 00:24:34.778 align:middle line:90%
And it changed my life.

00:24:34.778 --> 00:24:35.578 align:middle line:90%
[END PLAYBACK]

00:24:35.578 --> 00:24:37.580 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Changed his
life indeed, didn't it?

00:24:37.580 --> 00:24:38.380 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Indeed.

00:24:38.380 --> 00:24:39.310 align:middle line:90%
Indeed deeply.

00:24:39.310 --> 00:24:43.240 align:middle line:84%
And now he's dedicating to
study about consciousness.

00:24:43.240 --> 00:24:47.320 align:middle line:84%
And this sort of phenomena that
points to us that we are not

00:24:47.320 --> 00:24:49.060 align:middle line:90%
the brain actually.

00:24:49.060 --> 00:24:52.300 align:middle line:84%
Consciousness is not
a result of the brain.

00:24:52.300 --> 00:24:54.680 align:middle line:84%
Is not an epiphenomenon
of the brain.

00:24:54.680 --> 00:24:59.860 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's brilliant,
because scientists as Faggin

00:24:59.860 --> 00:25:03.580 align:middle line:84%
and as Kauffman that we
saw before, when they have

00:25:03.580 --> 00:25:07.270 align:middle line:84%
experiences, I guess a
true scientist must then

00:25:07.270 --> 00:25:08.770 align:middle line:90%
acknowledge, right?

00:25:08.770 --> 00:25:11.060 align:middle line:84%
I experienced something
that is different.

00:25:11.060 --> 00:25:12.970 align:middle line:90%
I never knew this existed.

00:25:12.970 --> 00:25:14.680 align:middle line:90%
I need to find explanation.

00:25:14.680 --> 00:25:21.100 align:middle line:84%
But what happens in real life
is that most scientists will not

00:25:21.100 --> 00:25:25.093 align:middle line:84%
admit that, will not say
because they are afraid--

00:25:25.093 --> 00:25:26.510 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: They
don't have answers.

00:25:26.510 --> 00:25:27.410 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: They
don't have answers,

00:25:27.410 --> 00:25:29.243 align:middle line:84%
but they also they are
afraid they are going

00:25:29.243 --> 00:25:31.870 align:middle line:90%
to be judged by their peers.

00:25:31.870 --> 00:25:34.160 align:middle line:84%
They are going to be
seen in a bad light.

00:25:34.160 --> 00:25:34.960 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:25:34.960 --> 00:25:37.827 align:middle line:84%
And people are going to
say now they are mystical

00:25:37.827 --> 00:25:38.785 align:middle line:90%
and they are becoming--

00:25:38.785 --> 00:25:39.785 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Ridicule them.

00:25:39.785 --> 00:25:41.890 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: Yes, and no
longer scientific.

00:25:41.890 --> 00:25:44.500 align:middle line:90%
So it's again a pity.

00:25:44.500 --> 00:25:48.910 align:middle line:84%
But I admire very much
these two gentlemen,

00:25:48.910 --> 00:25:51.040 align:middle line:84%
and that's why I
was talking to them

00:25:51.040 --> 00:25:55.720 align:middle line:84%
that could accept their
experiences, say the truth,

00:25:55.720 --> 00:25:58.480 align:middle line:84%
and say I do not know
exactly what happens,

00:25:58.480 --> 00:25:59.950 align:middle line:90%
but that's what happened.

00:25:59.950 --> 00:26:04.570 align:middle line:84%
And let's look for answers
in very technical ways.

00:26:04.570 --> 00:26:06.800 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: And that's happening
to millions of people.

00:26:06.800 --> 00:26:07.600 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Millions.

00:26:07.600 --> 00:26:08.400 align:middle line:90%
Millions.

00:26:08.400 --> 00:26:09.670 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: It's amazing.

00:26:09.670 --> 00:26:11.980 align:middle line:90%
What is VELO?

00:26:11.980 --> 00:26:15.560 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: VELO is a method
to work with energy.

00:26:15.560 --> 00:26:18.460 align:middle line:84%
I was saying that
the key to all--

00:26:18.460 --> 00:26:20.230 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: Did you develop this?

00:26:20.230 --> 00:26:21.160 align:middle line:90%
Did you develop it?

00:26:21.160 --> 00:26:23.050 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: Yes, I
developed this method.

00:26:23.050 --> 00:26:27.130 align:middle line:84%
But I developed based
on existing techniques,

00:26:27.130 --> 00:26:31.690 align:middle line:84%
because this method is
based on a technique that

00:26:31.690 --> 00:26:33.760 align:middle line:84%
is there from the
time of Buddha,

00:26:33.760 --> 00:26:36.610 align:middle line:84%
and have been used in
many different areas.

00:26:36.610 --> 00:26:40.360 align:middle line:84%
But people would just
do it in very let's

00:26:40.360 --> 00:26:45.370 align:middle line:84%
say eerie ways, just
trying to do something.

00:26:45.370 --> 00:26:47.315 align:middle line:84%
Each of them using a
different approach.

00:26:47.315 --> 00:26:48.940 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: What does
it stand for, VELO?

00:26:48.940 --> 00:26:52.450 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: VELO, it's Voluntary,
Energetic, Longitudinal,

00:26:52.450 --> 00:26:54.910 align:middle line:84%
Oscillation, which
pretty much describes

00:26:54.910 --> 00:26:56.710 align:middle line:90%
what the technique does.

00:26:56.710 --> 00:26:58.820 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Sounds pretty
scientific to me.

00:26:58.820 --> 00:26:59.620 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Yes.

00:26:59.620 --> 00:27:02.200 align:middle line:84%
But it's very simple
because something

00:27:02.200 --> 00:27:03.730 align:middle line:90%
we do at will, voluntary.

00:27:03.730 --> 00:27:05.650 align:middle line:90%
Energetic, it's our energy.

00:27:05.650 --> 00:27:09.250 align:middle line:84%
Longitudinal, because it's
longitudinal in our body.

00:27:09.250 --> 00:27:11.780 align:middle line:84%
And oscillation,
because it keeps moving.

00:27:11.780 --> 00:27:14.830 align:middle line:84%
So it's a movement of
energy inside of our bodies

00:27:14.830 --> 00:27:18.290 align:middle line:90%
that goes upwards and downwards.

00:27:18.290 --> 00:27:20.320 align:middle line:90%
And this is ancient.

00:27:20.320 --> 00:27:22.360 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: It's a
workable technique?

00:27:22.360 --> 00:27:24.130 align:middle line:84%
>>NANCI: It's very
workable technique.

00:27:24.130 --> 00:27:28.490 align:middle line:84%
And what happened is that
the fears that I had,

00:27:28.490 --> 00:27:30.760 align:middle line:84%
and when we think
of what is the key

00:27:30.760 --> 00:27:32.770 align:middle line:84%
to have all of these
phenomena, and the key

00:27:32.770 --> 00:27:36.070 align:middle line:84%
to be able to really master
the out-of-body experience.

00:27:36.070 --> 00:27:39.220 align:middle line:84%
And to really know what to
do when you are out there.

00:27:39.220 --> 00:27:41.060 align:middle line:90%
And how things are happening.

00:27:41.060 --> 00:27:47.350 align:middle line:84%
This technique is so important
because it gives one almost

00:27:47.350 --> 00:27:51.760 align:middle line:84%
like a fitness workout
of the whole energy body,

00:27:51.760 --> 00:27:57.430 align:middle line:84%
this exact energy that is
connecting us here in this body

00:27:57.430 --> 00:28:00.220 align:middle line:84%
as a consciousness
attached to this body,

00:28:00.220 --> 00:28:02.920 align:middle line:84%
and the non-physical
astral body.

00:28:02.920 --> 00:28:05.080 align:middle line:84%
And then what happens
with this technique

00:28:05.080 --> 00:28:08.530 align:middle line:84%
is that when I
was practicing it,

00:28:08.530 --> 00:28:11.980 align:middle line:84%
like I said in
very loose ways, I

00:28:11.980 --> 00:28:15.520 align:middle line:84%
started noticing that there were
some ways that I would do it

00:28:15.520 --> 00:28:18.470 align:middle line:90%
that would give me more results.

00:28:18.470 --> 00:28:22.520 align:middle line:84%
And I then started
practicing that way.

00:28:22.520 --> 00:28:25.460 align:middle line:84%
And later on, I
decided to research

00:28:25.460 --> 00:28:28.520 align:middle line:84%
what was the best way
to do this technique?

00:28:28.520 --> 00:28:31.620 align:middle line:84%
Because, George, let
me share this with you.

00:28:31.620 --> 00:28:32.900 align:middle line:90%
It's very nice.

00:28:32.900 --> 00:28:35.630 align:middle line:84%
I was then afraid
that I told you

00:28:35.630 --> 00:28:38.030 align:middle line:84%
got traumatized from
those experiences,

00:28:38.030 --> 00:28:39.530 align:middle line:84%
sensing those
entities, and there

00:28:39.530 --> 00:28:44.450 align:middle line:84%
are some situations that happen
that they seem out of a movie.

00:28:44.450 --> 00:28:45.420 align:middle line:90%
>>GEORGE: A bad movie.

00:28:45.420 --> 00:28:46.940 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Bad movie.

00:28:46.940 --> 00:28:50.990 align:middle line:84%
And to a point that I had
to sleep with the lights on.

00:28:50.990 --> 00:28:52.730 align:middle line:90%
I was like 25.

00:28:52.730 --> 00:28:54.260 align:middle line:84%
I had to sleep
with the lights on.

00:28:54.260 --> 00:28:56.160 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: 25 years old
and you had the lights on.

00:28:56.160 --> 00:28:56.960 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Yes.

00:28:56.960 --> 00:29:00.562 align:middle line:84%
And some places I would go
and I wouldn't sleep at all.

00:29:00.562 --> 00:29:03.020 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: I bet you didn't go
into closets either, did you?

00:29:03.020 --> 00:29:04.020 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: No, not at all.

00:29:04.020 --> 00:29:05.570 align:middle line:90%
Not even look at them sometimes.

00:29:05.570 --> 00:29:07.970 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes I--
long corridors,

00:29:07.970 --> 00:29:09.770 align:middle line:90%
they would be very frightening.

00:29:09.770 --> 00:29:12.800 align:middle line:84%
And it's amazing how
some horror movies,

00:29:12.800 --> 00:29:15.905 align:middle line:84%
they know what to pick
to impress people.

00:29:15.905 --> 00:29:17.780 align:middle line:84%
Of course, because they
hear stories and they

00:29:17.780 --> 00:29:20.850 align:middle line:84%
know what people are afraid
of and what they experience.

00:29:20.850 --> 00:29:21.750 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:29:21.750 --> 00:29:24.840 align:middle line:84%
But then I learned
this technique.

00:29:24.840 --> 00:29:28.860 align:middle line:84%
And then when I started
doing it, like in two weeks,

00:29:28.860 --> 00:29:31.110 align:middle line:90%
I was no longer afraid.

00:29:31.110 --> 00:29:33.840 align:middle line:84%
It was something out
of a miracle to me.

00:29:33.840 --> 00:29:35.760 align:middle line:84%
>>GEORGE: Did it help
you go out of the body?

00:29:35.760 --> 00:29:36.560 align:middle line:90%
>>NANCI: Yes.

00:29:36.560 --> 00:29:38.400 align:middle line:84%
Then I start
regaining the control

00:29:38.400 --> 00:29:43.390 align:middle line:84%
to go out of the body at will,
because spontaneously, this

00:29:43.390 --> 00:29:44.190 align:middle line:90%
happens.

00:29:44.190 --> 00:29:47.260 align:middle line:84%
But I wanted to be able
to perform it at will.

00:29:47.260 --> 00:29:50.560 align:middle line:84%
And I would be able to
go to a place by myself.

00:29:50.560 --> 00:29:54.360 align:middle line:84%
Even a place that I don't know
completely dark, I was OK.

00:29:54.360 --> 00:29:58.440 align:middle line:84%
And if I would sense something
that would seem fearful,

00:29:58.440 --> 00:29:59.825 align:middle line:90%
I knew what to do.

00:29:59.825 --> 00:30:01.200 align:middle line:84%
